drivers. For example, the <olink targetdoc="refman7" targetptr="ssd-7d" remap="external"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>ssd</refentrytitle><manvolnum>7D</manvolnum></citerefentry></olink> driver
has many code paths by which <literal>EIO</literal> may be returned. <acronym>FBT</acronym> can be easily used to determine the precise code path that resulted
in an error condition, as shown in the following example:</para><programlisting>fbt:ssd::return
/arg1 == EIO/
